OL,4,Cof pandemic on healthcare
OL,6,F"Despite the narrative pedalled by
OL,7,Fthose in charge that the UK coped, the
OL,8,Fsad fact is people died unnecessarily.
OL,10,F"Groups like the disabled and the
OL,11,Felderly were written off because it
OL,12,Fwas considered that their lives were
OL,13,Fnot worth saving."
OL,15,FIn July, the inquiry's first report
OL,16,Finto preparedness for a pandemic found
OL,17,Fthe UK Government and the civil
OL,18,Fservice "failed" the public due to
OL,19,F"significant flaws".
